Ask HN: What to Do with Duplicate Posts?
text:
I've posted something (https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=34465220) and it got marked immediately as duplicate.

I'm fine with this since it is a duplicate. I wonder what is a good practice for handling duplicates? Should I delete my post?

I know taht different online communities have different take on deleting content (Stack Overflow, Reddit, etc.).

What is HN recommendation?
